# POS Frontend ↔ Backend Integration — Walkthrough

## Summary

Successfully connected the entire POS React frontend (20+ pages) to the Express/MongoDB backend (16 modules) with full CRUD operations, JWT authentication, and real-time data persistence.

---

## What Was Built

### Phase 1: API Infrastructure (14 files created)

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `services/api.js` | Core HTTP client with JWT token management, auto-refresh on 401, structured error handling, query string builder |
| `services/auth.service.js` | Login, register, password change, token refresh, logout |
| `services/product.service.js` | Product CRUD → `/api/v1/products` |
| `services/supplier.service.js` | Supplier CRUD → `/api/v1/suppliers` |
| `services/customer.service.js` | Customer CRUD → `/api/v1/customers` |
| `services/sale.service.js` | Sales + returns → `/api/v1/sales` |
| `services/purchase.service.js` | Purchase invoices → `/api/v1/purchases` |
| `services/expense.service.js` | Expenses → `/api/v1/expenses` |
| `services/stock.service.js` | Stock view/returns/corrections → `/api/v1/stock` |
| `services/credit.service.js` | Supplier & customer credits → `/api/v1/credits` |
| `services/formulation.service.js` | Formulations CRUD → `/api/v1/formulations` |
| `services/settings.service.js` | Settings get/update → `/api/v1/settings` |
| `services/cash-adjustment.service.js` | Cash adjustments → `/api/v1/cash-adjustments` |
| `services/user.service.js` | User management → `/api/v1/users` |

### Phase 2: Authentication System (4 files)

- **`contexts/AuthContext.jsx`** — React context providing user/role state, login/logout, persistence via localStorage
- **`features/auth/LoginPage.jsx`** — Professional login page with dark gradient, password eye toggle, loading spinner, bilingual support
- **`App.jsx`** — Wrapped with `AuthProvider`, configured React Query defaults
- **`routes/Routes.jsx`** — `ProtectedRoute` wrapper redirects unauthenticated users to `/login`

### Phase 3: React Query Hooks (12 files)

Each hook provides `useQuery` for fetching (with loading/error states) and `useMutation` for mutations (with cache invalidation and toast notifications):

`useProducts`, `useSuppliers`, `useCustomers`, `useSales`, `usePurchases`, `useExpenses`, `useStock`, `useCredits`, `useFormulations`, `useSettings`, `useCashAdjustments`, `useUsers`

### Phase 4: Page Integration (20 pages modified)

Every page was rewired from local/mock state to real backend API calls:

| Page | Key Integration |
|---|---|
| **AddProductPage** | `POST /products` on save, form reset on success |
| **ViewProductsPage** | `GET /products` with search filters, inline edit via `PATCH` |
| **SalesPage** | Customer dropdown from DB, product code auto-lookup, `POST /sales` |
| **SalesReturnPage** | Product lookup, `POST /sales/return` |
| **SalesReportPage** | `GET /sales` with date filters, view bill detail |
| **PurchaseInvoicePage** | Supplier dropdown, barcode lookup, `POST /purchases` |
| **ViewPurchaseInvoicePage** | `GET /purchases` with multiple search modes |
| **AddSupplierPage** | `POST /suppliers` with form reset |
| **AddCustomerPage** | `POST /customers` with form reset |
| **AddFormulationPage** | `POST /formulations` with form reset |
| **AddUserPage** | `POST /auth/register`, `GET /users` for list |
| **ExpensePage** | `POST /expenses`, `GET /expenses`, `PATCH /:id/approve` |
| **StockPage** | `GET /stock` with search filters |
| **StockReturnPage** | Product lookup, `POST /stock/return` |
| **StockCorrectionPage** | Product lookup, `POST /stock/correction` |
| **SupplierCreditPage** | `POST /credits/supplier`, list from DB |
| **CustomerCreditPage** | Customer dropdown, `POST /credits/customer` |
| **CashAdjustmentPage** | `POST /cash-adjustments`, list from DB |
| **DeleteProductsPage** | Search product, `DELETE /products/:id` |
| **SettingsPage** | `GET /settings` on mount, `PATCH /settings` on save |

