## Architecture

```
Frontend (React)                     Backend (Express/MongoDB)
─────────────────                    ─────────────────────────
Page Component                       
  └─ React Query Hook                
      └─ Service Module              
          └─ api.js (fetch)  ──→  API Route → Controller → Service → Model → MongoDB
              ↑                       
          JWT Token (localStorage)    
```

## How to Test End-to-End

1. Start backend: `cd POS-Backend && npm run dev` (port 5000)
2. Start frontend: `cd POS && npm run dev` (port 6100)
3. Register a user via backend or use existing credentials
4. Login at `http://localhost:6100/login`
5. Add a product → verify it appears in View Products
6. Create a sale → verify it appears in Sales Report
